===Etymology===
八 is [[two]] bent lines that signal ''[[divide]]''. [[eight|Eight]] is the single-digit number that can be [[divided]] by [[two]] the greatest number of times.

===Han character===
{{Han char|rn=12|rad=八|as=00|sn=2|four=8000<sub>0</sub>|canj=竹人 (HO)}}

# [[eight]]
# [[all around]], [[all]] [[sides]]
# KangXi radical [[Index:Chinese radical/八|八]]

====Usage notes====
Minor strokes in the shape of ハ/八, as in the top of [[劵]], can be referred to 八. These are very frequently simplified to [[丷]]. Contrast [[劵]]/[[券]], and different forms of {{Jpan|[[鬲]]}}/{{Hans|鬲}}.
